And the most important thing is madam your availability to us , Nobody afraid to go and share the subject matters with you . Because we might not get problems during the lecture time . Every time after a mid exam , you have discussed the paper in next class . That is perfect . That helps to correct our mistakes , and to get proper idea of your point of view to the question . Because different people has different views to the same problem . So we were able to create a common good view by discussing the problems . Thank you madam ,

column2: This is one of those modules that should be placed as an example as what an excellent college module is . As a CSE student , I was always very skeptical on learning a mechanical module . Hence , I applaud for uploading recorded lectures so they can download them anytime they want . These session could be helpful to clarify the contents since students prefer voice communication over messages when it comes to learning .

column2: Lectures were well organized with presentations to back them up . The in class examples helped to understand the subject matter in a more interactive way because Ms Marcia went around the class asking questions . The lectures were quite clear . But the projections on that white background were not sometimes clearly visible to the people in the back rows . Ms. Marcia encouraged us to ask questions if there 's any doubt and proceeded with the lectures in a more interactive manner . The lecture slides were uploaded to the moodle every week . And I think it would be much better if you could upload them on Sunday evening because then us the students will have time to go through the slides before coming to the lecture .

column2: While the theory part of the module was okay , I want to share the story about how the software dev project stressed me out so much . I 'm not exaggerating , there were times I honestly could n't breathe . I wish you had informed us from the beginning about the technologies we 'd need , and warned us to get them properly set up in advance . ( In my case , there was problem after problem setting up localhost and the databases on my laptop , and there were so many times I had to rely on others ' work and panicked that I would fail this module 's CA ) We were so lost when it came to learning all those new things at once . It would have been better if the OOSD practical slots were used to actually teach us how to use PHP , MySQL type technology in the perspective of web development , instead of having outsiders come and do those loosely structured workshops which were from a general perspective . I feel like it would have been so helpful to learn them with some structure , rather than us haphazardly googling and putting together pieces of code to make the project . Another thing - Not only me but most of the others agree - the Zoom evaluations for the project were the worst thing we 've been through in the semester . They stressed us all out so much . I believe the reps sent feedback asking not to evaluate the project during the online period , but they were done anyway . I do n't know , maybe I have mental problems , but that project has been the single most stressful thing in my university life . And this was during the corona vacation . I ca n't imagine how much worse it would have been if the regular semester had been going on . I 'm sorry for getting so upset on here . I understand that you are trying to do the best , and , of course software dev can not be taught without a project like this . I just want to say , please try to make it easier for the next batches . Give them some structure from the beginning . Thanks for reading this .

column2: While the theory part of the module was okay , I want to share the story about how the software dev project stressed me out so much . I 'm not exaggerating , there were times I honestly could n't breathe . I wish you had informed us from the beginning about the technologies we 'd need , and warned us to get them properly set up in advance . ( In my case , there was problem after problem setting up localhost and the databases on my laptop , and there were so many times I had to rely on others ' work and panicked that I would fail this module 's CA ) We were so lost when it came to learning all those new things at once . It would have been better if the OOSD practical slots were used to actually teach us how to use PHP , MySQL type technology in the perspective of web development , instead of having outsiders come and do those loosely structured workshops which were from a general perspective . I feel like it would have been so helpful to learn them with some structure , rather than us haphazardly googling and putting together pieces of code to make the project . Another thing - Not only me but most of the others agree - the Zoom evaluations for the project were the worst thing we 've been through in the semester . They stressed us all out so much . I believe the reps sent feedback asking not to evaluate the project during the online period , but they were done anyway . I do n't know , maybe I have mental problems , but that project has been the single most stressful thing in my university life . And this was during the corona vacation . I ca n't imagine how much worse it would have been if the regular semester had been going on . I 'm sorry for getting so upset on here . I understand that you are trying to do the best , and , of course software dev can not be taught without a project like this . I just want to say , please try to make it easier for the next batches . Give them some structure from the beginning . Thanks for reading this .

column2: While the theory part of the module was okay , I want to share the story about how the software dev project stressed me out so much . I 'm not exaggerating , there were times I honestly could n't breathe . I wish you had informed us from the beginning about the technologies we 'd need , and warned us to get them properly set up in advance . ( In my case , there was problem after problem setting up localhost and the databases on my laptop , and there were so many times I had to rely on others ' work and panicked that I would fail this module 's CA ) We were so lost when it came to learning all those new things at once . It would have been better if the OOSD practical slots were used to actually teach us how to use PHP , MySQL type technology in the perspective of web development , instead of having outsiders come and do those loosely structured workshops which were from a general perspective . I feel like it would have been so helpful to learn them with some structure , rather than us haphazardly googling and putting together pieces of code to make the project . Another thing - Not only me but most of the others agree - the Zoom evaluations for the project were the worst thing we 've been through in the semester . They stressed us all out so much . I believe the reps sent feedback asking not to evaluate the project during the online period , but they were done anyway . I do n't know , maybe I have mental problems , but that project has been the single most stressful thing in my university life . And this was during the corona vacation . I ca n't imagine how much worse it would have been if the regular semester had been going on . I 'm sorry for getting so upset on here . I understand that you are trying to do the best , and , of course software dev can not be taught without a project like this . I just want to say , please try to make it easier for the next batches . Give them some structure from the beginning . Thanks for reading this .

column2: While the theory part of the module was okay , I want to share the story about how the software dev project stressed me out so much . I 'm not exaggerating , there were times I honestly could n't breathe . I wish you had informed us from the beginning about the technologies we 'd need , and warned us to get them properly set up in advance . ( In my case , there was problem after problem setting up localhost and the databases on my laptop , and there were so many times I had to rely on others ' work and panicked that I would fail this module 's CA ) We were so lost when it came to learning all those new things at once . It would have been better if the OOSD practical slots were used to actually teach us how to use PHP , MySQL type technology in the perspective of web development , instead of having outsiders come and do those loosely structured workshops which were from a general perspective . I feel like it would have been so helpful to learn them with some structure , rather than us haphazardly googling and putting together pieces of code to make the project . Another thing - Not only me but most of the others agree - the Zoom evaluations for the project were the worst thing we 've been through in the semester . They stressed us all out so much . I believe the reps sent feedback asking not to evaluate the project during the online period , but they were done anyway . I do n't know , maybe I have mental problems , but that project has been the single most stressful thing in my university life . And this was during the corona vacation . I ca n't imagine how much worse it would have been if the regular semester had been going on . I 'm sorry for getting so upset on here . I understand that you are trying to do the best , and , of course software dev can not be taught without a project like this . I just want to say , please try to make it easier for the next batches . Give them some structure from the beginning . Thanks for reading this .

column2: While the theory part of the module was okay , I want to share the story about how the software dev project stressed me out so much . I 'm not exaggerating , there were times I honestly could n't breathe . I wish you had informed us from the beginning about the technologies we 'd need , and warned us to get them properly set up in advance . ( In my case , there was problem after problem setting up localhost and the databases on my laptop , and there were so many times I had to rely on others ' work and panicked that I would fail this module 's CA ) We were so lost when it came to learning all those new things at once . It would have been better if the OOSD practical slots were used to actually teach us how to use PHP , MySQL type technology in the perspective of web development , instead of having outsiders come and do those loosely structured workshops which were from a general perspective . I feel like it would have been so helpful to learn them with some structure , rather than us haphazardly googling and putting together pieces of code to make the project . Another thing - Not only me but most of the others agree - the Zoom evaluations for the project were the worst thing we 've been through in the semester . They stressed us all out so much . I believe the reps sent feedback asking not to evaluate the project during the online period , but they were done anyway . I do n't know , maybe I have mental problems , but that project has been the single most stressful thing in my university life . And this was during the corona vacation . I ca n't imagine how much worse it would have been if the regular semester had been going on . I 'm sorry for getting so upset on here . I understand that you are trying to do the best , and , of course software dev can not be taught without a project like this . I just want to say , please try to make it easier for the next batches . Give them some structure from the beginning . Thanks for reading this .

column2: OOP is undoubtedly the most important module and we started our semester project ( Swimming Competition ) with a great joy with the intention to do a great creation by the semester end . But complex topics like Concurrency come , lectures went really really fast and the most of us could not grab much from the lecture . We noticed that the lecturer is trying to cover all the slides within the day and to explain the topics for us only if time permits . But that attempt was not so successful . Lecturers did their best , we know ! But time allocated for the subject is not enough ; or there must be something wrong in somewhere-else . We understood this subject only at the last week of the semester . But when we get the big picture , we were late ! For the project , we could not apply things we learned during last 2 weeks , so how can it measure our true learning ? It was a so tight schedule ! ! ! At the end of the semester , all the lecturers are only concentrating on covering the slides and to finish getting the continuous assessment marks of ours . We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !

column2: OOP is undoubtedly the most important module and we started our semester project ( Swimming Competition ) with a great joy with the intention to do a great creation by the semester end . But complex topics like Concurrency come , lectures went really really fast and the most of us could not grab much from the lecture . We noticed that the lecturer is trying to cover all the slides within the day and to explain the topics for us only if time permits . But that attempt was not so successful . Lecturers did their best , we know ! But time allocated for the subject is not enough ; or there must be something wrong in somewhere-else . We understood this subject only at the last week of the semester . But when we get the big picture , we were late ! For the project , we could not apply things we learned during last 2 weeks , so how can it measure our true learning ? It was a so tight schedule ! ! ! At the end of the semester , all the lecturers are only concentrating on covering the slides and to finish getting the continuous assessment marks of ours . We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !

column2: OOP is undoubtedly the most important module and we started our semester project ( Swimming Competition ) with a great joy with the intention to do a great creation by the semester end . But complex topics like Concurrency come , lectures went really really fast and the most of us could not grab much from the lecture . We noticed that the lecturer is trying to cover all the slides within the day and to explain the topics for us only if time permits . But that attempt was not so successful . Lecturers did their best , we know ! But time allocated for the subject is not enough ; or there must be something wrong in somewhere-else . We understood this subject only at the last week of the semester . But when we get the big picture , we were late ! For the project , we could not apply things we learned during last 2 weeks , so how can it measure our true learning ? It was a so tight schedule ! ! ! At the end of the semester , all the lecturers are only concentrating on covering the slides and to finish getting the continuous assessment marks of ours . We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !

column2: OOP is undoubtedly the most important module and we started our semester project ( Swimming Competition ) with a great joy with the intention to do a great creation by the semester end . But complex topics like Concurrency come , lectures went really really fast and the most of us could not grab much from the lecture . We noticed that the lecturer is trying to cover all the slides within the day and to explain the topics for us only if time permits . But that attempt was not so successful . Lecturers did their best , we know ! But time allocated for the subject is not enough ; or there must be something wrong in somewhere-else . We understood this subject only at the last week of the semester . But when we get the big picture , we were late ! For the project , we could not apply things we learned during last 2 weeks , so how can it measure our true learning ? It was a so tight schedule ! ! ! At the end of the semester , all the lecturers are only concentrating on covering the slides and to finish getting the continuous assessment marks of ours . We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !

column2: OOP is undoubtedly the most important module and we started our semester project ( Swimming Competition ) with a great joy with the intention to do a great creation by the semester end . But complex topics like Concurrency come , lectures went really really fast and the most of us could not grab much from the lecture . We noticed that the lecturer is trying to cover all the slides within the day and to explain the topics for us only if time permits . But that attempt was not so successful . Lecturers did their best , we know ! But time allocated for the subject is not enough ; or there must be something wrong in somewhere-else . We understood this subject only at the last week of the semester . But when we get the big picture , we were late ! For the project , we could not apply things we learned during last 2 weeks , so how can it measure our true learning ? It was a so tight schedule ! ! ! At the end of the semester , all the lecturers are only concentrating on covering the slides and to finish getting the continuous assessment marks of ours . We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !

column2: OOP is undoubtedly the most important module and we started our semester project ( Swimming Competition ) with a great joy with the intention to do a great creation by the semester end . But complex topics like Concurrency come , lectures went really really fast and the most of us could not grab much from the lecture . We noticed that the lecturer is trying to cover all the slides within the day and to explain the topics for us only if time permits . But that attempt was not so successful . Lecturers did their best , we know ! But time allocated for the subject is not enough ; or there must be something wrong in somewhere-else . We understood this subject only at the last week of the semester . But when we get the big picture , we were late ! For the project , we could not apply things we learned during last 2 weeks , so how can it measure our true learning ? It was a so tight schedule ! ! ! At the end of the semester , all the lecturers are only concentrating on covering the slides and to finish getting the continuous assessment marks of ours . We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !

column2: OOP is undoubtedly the most important module and we started our semester project ( Swimming Competition ) with a great joy with the intention to do a great creation by the semester end . But complex topics like Concurrency come , lectures went really really fast and the most of us could not grab much from the lecture . We noticed that the lecturer is trying to cover all the slides within the day and to explain the topics for us only if time permits . But that attempt was not so successful . Lecturers did their best , we know ! But time allocated for the subject is not enough ; or there must be something wrong in somewhere-else . We understood this subject only at the last week of the semester . But when we get the big picture , we were late ! For the project , we could not apply things we learned during last 2 weeks , so how can it measure our true learning ? It was a so tight schedule ! ! ! At the end of the semester , all the lecturers are only concentrating on covering the slides and to finish getting the continuous assessment marks of ours . We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !

column2: OOP is undoubtedly the most important module and we started our semester project ( Swimming Competition ) with a great joy with the intention to do a great creation by the semester end . But complex topics like Concurrency come , lectures went really really fast and the most of us could not grab much from the lecture . We noticed that the lecturer is trying to cover all the slides within the day and to explain the topics for us only if time permits . But that attempt was not so successful . Lecturers did their best , we know ! But time allocated for the subject is not enough ; or there must be something wrong in somewhere-else . We understood this subject only at the last week of the semester . But when we get the big picture , we were late ! For the project , we could not apply things we learned during last 2 weeks , so how can it measure our true learning ? It was a so tight schedule ! ! ! At the end of the semester , all the lecturers are only concentrating on covering the slides and to finish getting the continuous assessment marks of ours . We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !

column2: OOP is undoubtedly the most important module and we started our semester project ( Swimming Competition ) with a great joy with the intention to do a great creation by the semester end . But complex topics like Concurrency come , lectures went really really fast and the most of us could not grab much from the lecture . We noticed that the lecturer is trying to cover all the slides within the day and to explain the topics for us only if time permits . But that attempt was not so successful . Lecturers did their best , we know ! But time allocated for the subject is not enough ; or there must be something wrong in somewhere-else . We understood this subject only at the last week of the semester . But when we get the big picture , we were late ! For the project , we could not apply things we learned during last 2 weeks , so how can it measure our true learning ? It was a so tight schedule ! ! ! At the end of the semester , all the lecturers are only concentrating on covering the slides and to finish getting the continuous assessment marks of ours . We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !

We came to CSE with the trust you made in us through the first semester well-structured lecture series . But now we see this as a race ; not a true teaching-learning process . Honor Code pledges were taken at the beginning to make sure that we learn everything by our own self . We thought we came to heaven like department where the lecturers help us to grow and we thought we are gon na be one big family . But now we know it is just marketing . We love learning these subjects ; the truth is these are not hard for us . But please give students some time to go to the depth and do things with a better-understanding ! Covering the module and doing the CA evaluations can be done after students learn the subject properly . If our department continues this way for future , you would one day make a stack-overflow generation ; not a skilled and creative workforce ! My request is to give students the freedom to learn concepts and do things creatively , then they will master in the subject . Is n't it the ultimate purpose of both parties ? ? Please give us support to learn things properly first , we really want to learn , we have that passion for the subject ! Please make that environment at CSE ! ! ! Thank you very much madam for everything you taught us throughout the semester ! We know you did a great job for us , although the module was so lengthy for this semester ! ! Hope our feedback would help the administration to make a better CSE Dept tomorrow !
